-- China to Seek to Curb Hot Money Inflows, State Council Researcher Ba Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-25T15:49:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-25/china-to-curb-hot-money-inflows-after-interest-rate-rise-pboc-s-ba-says.html
China’s central bank will enhance
regulations to prevent hot money from entering the country as a
result of increases in interest rates,  Ba Shusong , a researcher
at the State Council’s Development Research Center, told state
television today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
